gurmukhi: myGjinn Sbdwid aucwrn kIjIAY ]jwcr kih kih nwQ Sbd ko dIjIAY ]S`qRu Sbd khu qwko AMq aucwrIAY ]ho skl qupk ky nwm pRbIn ibcwrIAY ]906]
transliteration: Meghjanin Shabadaadh Ouchaaran Keejeeai|| Jaachar Kah(i) Kah(i) Naath Shabad Ko Deejeeai|| Shattru Shabad Kauh Taako Ant Oucdareeai|| Ho Sakal Toupak Ke Naam Prabeen Bicdareeai||906||
translation: Saying firstly the word “Meghjanin”, then add the words “Jaachar, naath and shatru” and consider all the names of Tupak.906.

gurmukhi: swrsuqI Sbdwid aucwro ]jwcr kih nwiek pd fwro ]S`qRu Sbd khu bhur Bix`jY ]nwm qupk ky sB lih il`jY ]907]
transliteration: Saarsoutishabadaadh Oucdaro|| Jaachar Kah(i) Naaik Pad Daro|| Shattru Shabad Kauh Bahur Bhanijjai|| Naam Toupak Ke Sabh Lah(i) Lijjai||907||
translation: Utter firstly the word “Sarasvati” and then speak the words “Jaachar-nayak-shatru” and in this way speak all the names of Tupak.907.

gurmukhi: gMg BytnI Awid aucwro ]jwcr kih nwiek pd fwro ]S`qRu Sbd khu bhur Bix`jY ]nwm qupk ky skl kih`jY ]908]
transliteration: Gadg Bhetaniaadh Oucdaro|| Jaachar Kah(i) Naaik Pad Daro|| Shattru Shabad Kauh Bahur Bhanijjai|| Naam Toupak Ke Sakal Kahijjai||908||
translation: Say firstly the word “Gang-bhetani” and then utter the words “Jaachar-nayak-shatru” and in this way speak all the names of Tupak.908.

gurmukhi: Arnbwrinn Awid bKwnhu ]jwcr kih nwiek pd Twnhu ]S`qRu Sbd ko bhur aucwrhu ]nwm qupk ky skl ibcwrhu ]909]
transliteration: Arnbaarnin Aadh Bakhaanoh|| Jaachar Kah(i) Naaik Pad Thaandh|| Shattru Shabad Ko Bahur Oucdaroh|| Naam Toupak Ke Sakal Bicdaroh||909||
translation: Say firstly the word “Arun-vaarnin”, then add the words “Jaachar-nayak-shatru” and know all the names of Tupak.909.

gurmukhi: Arux bwrnI Awid bKwno ]jwcr kih nwiek pd Twno ]S`qRu Sbd khu bhur aucwro ]skl qupk ky nwm ibcwro ]910]
transliteration: Aroun Baarniaadh Bakhaano|| Jaachar Kah(i) Naaik Pad Thaano|| Shattru Shabad Kauh Bahur Oucdaro|| Sakal Toupak Ke Naam Bicdaro||910||
translation: Say firstly the word “Arun-vaarini”, then add the words “Jaachar-nayak-shatru” and know the names of Tupak.910.

gurmukhi: Arux AMbnIn Awid aucwrn kIjIAY ]jwcr kih kY nwQ Sbd ko dIjIAY ]S`qRu Sbd khu qwky AMq bKwnIAY ]ho skl qupk ky nwm sbu`D pRmwnIAY ]911]
transliteration: Aroun Anbnin Aadh Ouchaaran Keejeeai|| Jaachar Kah(i) Kai Naath Shabad Ko Deejeeai|| Shattru Shabad Kauh Taake Ant Bakhaaneeai|| Ho Sakal Toupak Ke Naam Soubuddh Pramaaneeai||911||
translation: Saying firstly the word “Arun-ambneen”, add the words “Jaachar-naath-shatru” and know all the names of Tupak.911.

gurmukhi: Arux qurMgin Awid aucwro ]jwcr kih nwiek pd fwro ]S`qRu Sbd khu bhur Bix`jY ]skl qupk ky nwm kih`jY ]912]
transliteration: Aroun Turanad(i) Aadh Oucdaro|| Jaachar Kah(i) Naaik Pad Daro|| Shattru Shabad Kauh Bahur Bhanijjai|| Sakal Toupak Ke Naam Kahijjai||912||
translation: Saying firstly the word “Arun-turangni”, add the words “Jaachar-nayak-shatru” and know all the names of Tupak.912.

gurmukhi: Awrkqw jlinn pd BwKo ]jwcr kih nwiek pd rwKo ]S`qRu Sbd khu bhur Bix`jY ]sB sRI nwm qupk liK il`jY ]913]
transliteration: Aaraktaa Jalnin Pad Bhaakho|| Jaachar Kah(i) Naaik Pad Raakho|| Shattru Shabad Kauh Bahur Bhanijjai|| Sabh Srinaam Toupak Lakh(i) Lijjai||913||
translation: Saying firstly the word “Aarakat-jalni (Brahmputra), then add the words “Jaachar-nayak-shatru” and know the names of Tupak.913.

gurmukhi: Arun AMbnin Awid bKwnhu ]jwcr kih piq Sbd pRmwnhu ]S`qRu Sbd khu bhur aucwro ]nwm qupk ky skl ibcwro ]914]
transliteration: Aroun Anbnan(i) Aadh Bakhaanoh|| Jaachar Kah(i) Pat(i) Shabad Pramaanoh|| Shattru Shabad Kauh Bahur Oucdaro|| Naam Toupak Ke Sakal Bicdaro||914||
translation: Saying firstly the word “Arun-ambunani”, then utter the words “Jaachar-pati-shatru” and know all the names of Tupak.914.

gurmukhi: Arun pwnnI Awid Bix`jY ]jwcr kih nwiek pd id`jY ]Air pd qwky AMq bKwno ]nwm qupk ky sB jIA jwno ]915]
transliteration: Aroun Paananiaadh Bhanijjai|| Jaachar Kah(i) Naaik Pad Dijjai|| Ar(i) Pad Taake Ant Bakhaano|| Naam Toupak Ke Sabh Jeea Jaano||915||
translation: Saying firstly the word “Arun-paanini”, add the words “Jaachar-nayak-ari” and know all the names of Tupak.915.

gurmukhi: Arun jlnnI Awid bKwnhu ]jwcr kih piq Sbd pRmwnhu ]S`qRu Sbd ko bhur Bix`jY ]nwm qupk ky sB liK il`jY ]916]
transliteration: Aroun Paananiaadh Bakhaanoh|| Jaachar Kah(i) Pat(i) Shabad Pramaanoh|| Shattru Shabad Ko Bahur Bhanijjai|| Naam Toupak Ke Sabh Lakh(i) Lijjai||916||
translation: Saying firstly the word “Arun-jalnani”, add the words “Jaachar-pati-shatru” and know all the names of Tupak.916.
